title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER 1873 44-40, HIGHER % Org. Blue -NO RES circa 1882, MINTY BORE, 1876 1886
postcontent: On a true "NO RESERVE" $0.01 start auction I have a very nice Winchester Model 1873 sporting rifle chambered in the 44 W.C.F. (44-40) caliber. This rifle, serial #95839 is one of the first 3rd Model's made, being manufactured in 1882. The gun letters 100% correct with the Winchester factory ledgers housed at the Cody Firearms Museum. 1st Model 1873's were made to around 30,000 serial number range, 2nd Model's were from 30,000 to 90,000, and 3rd Model's from 90,000 to the end of production (720,610). This rifle has some of the early 1st and 2nd Model features, such as the early rear sight and a heavier #2 round barrel. One of every six 1873's made had a round barrel (octagon being standard). As for condition the receiver retains around 80% of its original bright blue finish with very light spotting in areas. The bluing looking much better in person as the camera lightens up the look of the finish some. The original 24", #2 heavy barrel and full magazine also retain around 80% of their original bluing. The original walnut stocks are in excellent condition, retaining most of their original finish, with minimal light handling marks. The wood to metal fit is tight and proud. The action is tight and smooth, mechanically like new. The hammer and lever springs are strong as new. The dustcover remains tight to the rail and slides flawlessly when cycled. The dustcover rail still retains much of its original bluing. The bore is in MINTY condition, showing a mirror shine with sharp rifling. I would rate it at 90%. The screws are excellent and many remain unturned. The dustcover screws is a little buggered. The hammer and lever retain faded case colors. The sights are original and in excellent condition. The brass carrier retains sharp edges showing minimal use. In all this is a very good example of an all original, unmolested and higher condition early 1873. I have provided over 90 photos and offer a 3 day inspection period so you can bid with confidence.
